|<------------------------------->[ BEGIN-CRFCF ]<------------------------------->|

NOTICE: UNAUTHORIZED MODIFICATION OF THIS DOCUMENT IS EXPRESSLY PROHIBITED. EDITING
PRIVILEGES ARE EXCLUSIVELY RESERVED FOR THE AUTHOR, DESIGNATED CONTRIBUTORS, AND
AUTHORIZED ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE AGENTS. DOCUMENT INTEGRITY IS SECURED BY A
CRYPTOGRAPHIC CHECKSUM; AUTOMATED VERIFICATION SCRIPTS ARE EMPLOYED TO DETECT AND
PREVENT UNAUTHORIZED ALTERATIONS.

0.  METADATA:

    - RFC:      CONCISE-RFC-000000
    - GROUP:    VS-SCRIPTS
    - TITLE:    CONCISE RFC FORMAT
    - ACRONYM:  CRFCF
    - AUTHOR:   RICHEVE BEBEDOR <richeve.bebedor+vs-scripts@gmail.com>
    - CATEGORY: SPECIFICATION
    - STATUS:   DRAFT
    - VERSION:  000000 (0.0.0)
    - CREATED:  2025-12-20
    - CHECKSUM: <SHA-256>

1.  Summary:

    This document defines the canonical structure, sections, and rules for all
    CONCISE-RFC-XXXXXX documents in this repository. It serves as the authoritative
    template for contributors, artificial intelligent agents, and tooling.

2.  Permission:

    NOTICE: PERMISSION TO USE, MODIFY, COPY, AND/OR DISTRIBUTE THIS DOCUMENT
    AND/OR REPOSITORY IS GRANTED UNDER THE TERMS OF THE LICENSE AGREEMENT
    SPECIFIED IN THE LICENSE FILE. PLEASE REFER TO THE LICENSE FILE FOR DETAILS.

3.  Contents:

    0.  METADATA ........................................................... 009
    1.  Summary ............................................................ 022
    2.  Permission ......................................................... 028
    3.  Contents ........................................................... 034
    4.  Document Status .................................................... 046
    5.  Normative Language ................................................. 057
    6.  Naming Conventions ................................................. 071
    7.  Structure .......................................................... 076
    8.  Compliance ......................................................... 354

4.  Document Status:

    - This document is a DRAFT repository-level RFC.
    - It is not an Internet Standards Track specification.
    - It is intended to enforce,

        - uniformity,
        - clarity,
        - conciseness,
        - and machine-parsable

      structure across all CONCISE-RFC-XXXXXX documents.

5.  Normative Language:

    - The key words,

        - MUST,
        - MUST NOT,
        - SHOULD,
        - and SHOULD NOT

      in this document SHOULD follow RFC-2119 and RFC-8174.
    - This document MUST NOT use MAY.
    - The key word "MUST" denotes "required".
    - The key word "SHOULD" denotes "optional".

6.  Naming Conventions:

    - CONCISE-RFC-XXXXXX document file names MUST be in ALL CAPS.

        Exceptions:
            - *.todo files
            - *.help files

    - All CONCISE-RFC-XXXXXX document file names MUST be one word.

        Exceptions:
            - *.todo files
            - *.help files

7.  Structure:

    - All CONCISE-RFC-XXXXXX documents MUST be in text format.

    - All CONCISE-RFC-XXXXXX documents MUST be encoded in UTF-8 without BOM.

    - All CONCISE-RFC-XXXXXX documents MUST use LF as the EOL style.

    - All CONCISE-RFC-XXXXXX documents MUST end with a trailing newline.

    - All CONCISE-RFC-XXXXXX documents MUST NOT exceed 997 lines of text.

    - All CONCISE-RFC-XXXXXX documents MUST be within 83 characters
      in column width per line.

    - All CONCISE-RFC-XXXXXX documents MUST start with,
        - 1 (|) pipe character, then
        - 1 less than (<) character, then
        - 31 hyphen (-) characters, then
        - 1 opening square bracket ([) character
        - followed by BEGIN-CRFCF surrounded by 1 space on each side, then
        - 1 closing square bracket (]) character
        - 31 hyphen (-) characters, then
        - 1 greater than (>) character, and then, lastly,
        - 1 (|) pipe character.

    - All CONCISE-RFC-XXXXXX documents MUST end with,
        - 1 (|) pipe character, then
        - 1 less than (<) character, then
        - 31 hyphen (-) characters, then
        - 1 opening square bracket ([) character
        - followed by ENDED-CRFCF surrounded by 1 space on each side, then
        - 1 closing square bracket (]) character
        - 31 hyphen (-) characters, then
        - 1 greater than (>) character, and then, lastly,
        - 1 (|) pipe character.

    - All CONCISE-RFC-XXXXXX documents MUST have the NOTICE for unauthorized
      modifications with the following format:

        NOTICE: UNAUTHORIZED MODIFICATION OF THIS DOCUMENT IS EXPRESSLY PROHIBITED.
        EDITING PRIVILEGES ARE EXCLUSIVELY RESERVED FOR THE AUTHOR, DESIGNATED
        CONTRIBUTORS, AND AUTHORIZED ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE AGENTS. DOCUMENT
        INTEGRITY IS SECURED BY A CRYPTOGRAPHIC CHECKSUM; AUTOMATED VERIFICATION
        SCRIPTS ARE EMPLOYED TO DETECT AND PREVENT UNAUTHORIZED ALTERATIONS.

        - This NOTICE format MUST NOT be modified.

    - All repositories MUST contain the following METADATA documents:

        - 5LAWS
        - AUTHOR
        - CHANGELOG

            - This MUST contain the changelog of this repository.
            - Each line entry MUST respect the 83 characters column width.
            - Each line entry SHOULD respect the conventional commits 1.0.0
              specification as described in this document:

                https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/

              with few caveats:

                - This document MUST only contain the following action types:

                    - specs

                        - These commits MUST only contain files and messages
                          regarding changes to the todo/ directory.

                    - tests

                        - These commits MUST only contain files and messages
                          regarding changes to the tests/ directory.

                    - issue

                        - These commits MUST only contain files and messages
                          regarding changes that is outside of todo/, tests/, and
                          helps/ directory.

                    - helps

                        - These commits MUST only contain files and messages
                          regarding changes to the helps/ directory.

                    - break

                        - These commits MUST only contain the VERSION file
                          and messages regarding changes to the VERSION file.

                - tests MUST be interpreted as test
                - helps MUST be interpreted as docs
                - revert MUST be interpreted as issue
                - fix MUST be interpreted as issue
                - feat MUST be interpreted as issue
                - perf MUST be interpreted as issue
                - ci MUST be interpreted as issue
                - style MUST be interpreted as issue
                - chore MUST be interpreted as issue
                - build MUST be interpreted as issue
                - specs MUST be interpreted as docs and chore combined
                - specs MUST be for issue specification only
                - break MUST be interpreted as a commit history break
                - commit history break provides historical grouping
                - All action types MUST have a character length of 5.

            - Each changelog item MUST be in this format:

                <YYYY-MM-DD> <action-type>: <concise-description>

                Example:

                    2025-12-20 specs: update documentation

            - Concise description MUST have a maximum character
              length of 65.
            - The format for each changelog item MUST consist of,

                - 10 characters date in YYYY-MM-DD format, followed by space then,
                - action type right padded to length 5, then colon and space then,
                - lastly, a maximum of 65 character length concise description.

        - CONTRIBUTING
        - CONTRIBUTORS
        - EMAIL
        - FLOW
        - FORMAT

            - This file itself.

        - INDEX

            - The target entry of this repository.

        - LICENSE

            - This MUST contain the license of this repository.
            - This MUST follow the FORMAT file.
            - This MUST only contain two sections, METADATA and License.

        - METADATA
        - ORIGIN
        - PRIVACY
        - README
        - REFERENCES
        - SECURITY
        - WEBSITE
        - VERSION

            - This MUST contain the version of this repository in SEMVER format.
            - SEMVER format MUST adhere to the format defined in,

                https://semver.org/

              with few caveats:

                - This MUST be in the RELEASE.MAJOR.MINOR format.
                - PATCH version MUST be interpreted as MINOR version.
                - CRITICAL changes MUST be interpreted as MAJOR version.
                - RELEASE version MUST start at zero.
                - A RELEASE version of zero MUST NOT be considered stable.
                - A RELEASE version of zero MUST NOT be used in production.
                - 99 MINOR versions MUST increment the MAJOR version.
                - 99 MAJOR versions MUST increment the RELEASE version.

            - Only the author MUST have the capability to update the VERSION file.
            - Version numbers MUST NOT reach 3 digits.


    - All single-line text formatted METADATA documents MUST be a single line
      with no line feed end of line and no final line feed.

    - All list text formatted METADATA documents MUST be multiple lines
      with line feed end of line and no final line feed.

    - All CONCISE-RFC-XXXXXX documents MUST follow this structure
      in this order:

        X.  METADATA:

            This MUST contain the metadata of this document.

            The metadata of this document MUST follow this format
            in this order:

            - RFC:      CONCISE-RFC-XXXXXX

                - This MUST be the RFC format version name of the FORMAT file
                  used by this document.

            - GROUP:    <GROUP PROJECT NAME>
            - TITLE:    <UNIQUE AND CONCISE DOCUMENT TITLE>

                - This MUST have a maximum of 5 letter word.

            - ACRONYM:  <UACDT>

                - This MUST be 5 alphanumeric characters uppercase format.

            - AUTHOR:   <FIRST NAME> <LAST NAME> <email>
            - CATEGORY: (SPECIFICATION | INFORMATIONAL | EXPERIMENTAL)
            - STATUS:   (DRAFT | REVIEW | STABLE | DEPRECATED | OBSOLETE)
            - VERSION:  XXXXXX <X.X.X>

                - This MUST be the version of this document.

            - CREATED:  <YYYY-MM-DD>
            - CHECKSUM: <SHA-256>

        X.  Summary:

            This MUST contain the abstract of this document.

        X.  License:

            - This MUST contain the license text of this document.
            - This MUST only be used on LICENSE document.
            - LICENSE document MUST only contain this and the METADATA section.

        X.  Permission:

            - This MUST define the permissions for using, modifying, copying, and
              distributing this document and/or this repository.
            - This MUST contain the NOTICE for permission in this format:

                NOTICE: PERMISSION TO USE, MODIFY, COPY, AND/OR DISTRIBUTE THIS
                DOCUMENT AND/OR REPOSITORY IS GRANTED UNDER THE TERMS OF THE
                LICENSE AGREEMENT SPECIFIED IN THE LICENSE FILE. PLEASE REFER TO
                THE LICENSE FILE FOR DETAILS.

            - This MUST be contained in all CONCISE-RFC-XXXXXX documents except the
              LICENSE file.

        X.  Contents:

            This MUST contain the table of contents of this document.

        X.  Document Status:

            This MUST contain the descriptive status of this document.

        X.  Normative Language:

            This MUST contain the normative language of this document.

        X.  Naming Conventions:

            This MUST contain the naming conventions of this document.

        X.  Structure:

            This MUST contain the structure of the repository and/or this document.

        X.  Compliance:

            This MUST contain the compliance of this document to this format,
            styles, principles, and tools which include any, but not limited, to
            artificial intelligent agent tools.

    - All CONCISE-RFC-XXXXXX documents MUST follow these principles:

        - Single Responsibility Principle. CONCISE-RFC-XXXXXX documents
          MUST address one and only one concern or feature.
        - Open-Closed Principle. CONCISE-RFC-XXXXXX documents MUST be open for
          extension but closed for modification. Once the status is STABLE, the
          CONCISE-RFC-XXXXXX documents MUST NOT be modified. New
          CONCISE-RFC-XXXXXX documents MUST be created for updates. If a
          CONCISE-RFC-XXXXXX document has issues, then the entire
          CONCISE-RFC-XXXXXX document MUST be marked for deprecation and a new
          CONCISE-RFC-XXXXXX document MUST be published.
        - Liskov Principle. <todo: Please fill this>
        - Interface Segregation Principle. <todo: Please fill this>
        - Dependency Inversion Principle. <todo: Please fill this>

    - All CONCISE-RFC-XXXXXX documents MUST follow this style:

        - Section headers MUST be clear, concise, and well-defined.
        - Section headers MUST always define one and only one meaning.
        - Section contents MUST only contain the following styles,
            - Descriptive paragraphs in normal conversational English language.
            - Descriptive paragraphs must not contain complex conversational
              English words.
            - Lists that start with 1 hyphen (-) character followed by a single
              space and then the list item.
            - Formatted structures that are different from this format.
        - All formatted structures with ordered components MUST be followed.

    - All repositories MUST contain the following basic directories,

        - .vscode/
        - .github/
        - .husky/
        - dist/
        - helps/
        - public/
        - scripts/
        - src/
        - template/
        - tests/
        - todo/

            - All todo files MUST follow CONCISE-RFC-XXXXXX.
            - All todo files MUST end with *.todo file extension.
            - All todo files MUST be interpreted as text files.
            - There are five issue categories for todo,

                - critical
                - major
                - minor
                - prototype
                - reported

            - All todo files MUST follow the file name format:

                <priority>-issue-<YYYY-MM-DD>-<short-title>.todo

                Example:

                    critical-issue-2025-12-21-fix-e2e-tests.todo

        - waste

8.  Compliance:

        - All artificial intelligent agents MUST read the FORMAT file.
        - All artificial intelligent agents MUST add the FORMAT file in their
          context list.
        - All artificial intelligent agents MUST follow the FORMAT file.
        - All artificial intelligent agents MUST respect the FORMAT file.
        - All artificial intelligent agents MUST NOT modify the FORMAT file.
        - All artificial intelligent agents MUST NOT modify the VERSION file.
        - All artificial intelligent agents MUST adhere to the normative language
          requirements in the FORMAT file.

|<------------------------------->[ ENDED-CRFCF ]<------------------------------->|
